beep: beep (Beep the pc speaker any number of ways)
beep:
beep: Beep allows the user to control the pc-speaker with precision,
beep: allowing different sounds to indicate different events. While it can
beep: be run quite happily on the commandline, it's intended place of
beep: residence is within shell/perl scripts, notifying the user when
beep: something interesting occurs. Of course, it has no notion of
beep: what's interesting, but it's real good at that notifying part.
beep:
beep: http://www.johnath.com/beep/
